---
import BaseLayout from '@layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import Section from '@components/layout/Section.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Privacy Policy — Kristian López"
  description="Privacy policy for lopezkristian.com — how data is handled, analytics opt-in, and your rights under GDPR."
  image="/og/og-home.png"
>
  <Section>
    <div class="max-w-3xl">
      <h1 class="mb-4 text-4xl font-bold text-text-primary">Privacy Policy</h1>
      <p class="mb-8 text-sm text-muted">Last updated: February 2026</p>

      <div class="prose max-w-none prose-headings:text-text-primary prose-p:text-muted prose-li:text-muted prose-a:text-violet-400 prose-strong:text-text-primary">
        <h2>1. Introduction</h2>
        <p>
          This Privacy Policy describes how lopezkristian.com handles information 
          when you visit it. I take your privacy seriously and aim to be transparent about what 
          data, if any, is collected.
        </p>

        <h2>2. What Data Is Collected</h2>
        <p>
          <strong class="text-text-primary">This site does not collect personal data by default.</strong> 
          There are no tracking cookies, no third-party analytics scripts, and no user accounts.
        </p>
        <p>
          If analytics are enabled via the PUBLIC_ANALYTICS_ID environment variable, 
          a privacy-first analytics tool (Plausible or Umami) may collect aggregate, anonymized 
          page view data. These tools do not use cookies and do not collect personal information.
        </p>

        <h2>3. Contact Form</h2>
        <p>
          If you submit the contact form, the data you provide (name, email, message) is sent
          to Web3Forms, a third-party form handling service. It is used solely to respond to your
          inquiry. See <a href="https://web3forms.com/privacy" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Web3Forms Privacy Policy</a> for details.
        </p>

        <h2>4. Third-Party Links</h2>
        <p>
          This site links to external services (GitHub, LinkedIn). Those services have their own 
          privacy policies. I am not responsible for their practices.
        </p>

        <h2>5. Your Rights (GDPR)</h2>
        <p>If you are in the EU, you have the right to:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>Access any data I hold about you</li>
          <li>Request correction or deletion of your data</li>
          <li>Object to processing</li>
          <li>Lodge a complaint with your local data protection authority</li>
        </ul>
        <p>
          To exercise any of these rights, contact me via the contact form.
        </p>

        <h2>6. Changes to This Policy</h2>
        <p>
          This policy may be updated occasionally. Significant changes will be noted at the top 
          of this page with the updated date.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </Section>
</BaseLayout>
